01:11:16.149 --> 01:11:28.149
There were no great stadiums here, so the multitudes reminding us of those who came to isolated places to hear Jesus, gathered out in the open under clear skies to listen to the message.

01:11:28.149 --> 01:11:38.149
That people from many different tribes and all parts of the land could meet with no fighting or bloodshed amazed the Africans, the police, and the Europeans.

01:11:38.149 --> 01:11:43.529
It was taken for granted however by the Christians who were in attendance.

01:11:44.529 --> 01:11:49.529
These witnesses of Jehovah, your Christian brothers, know what they believe.

01:11:49.529 --> 01:11:57.529
Can prove it from the Scriptures, or zealous in their activity, and considered it well worth the effort to come and hear the good message.

01:11:57.529 --> 01:12:27.500
145 persons were in attendance at a European assembly at this hall in Kittwee, northern Odesia, in December 1952, and at the African Assembly at Kittwee an amazing 20,000 were in attendance.

01:12:27.500 --> 01:12:35.500
Here again, in the heart of Africa there was no stadium, but that didn't stand in the way of these energetic witnesses for Jehovah.

01:12:35.500 --> 01:12:46.500
They cut enough material from nearby forests to make benches for more than 18,000 people, a quarter of the seating capacity of New York's famed Yankee Stadium.

01:12:46.500 --> 01:12:58.550
Yet this was not in one of the world's great cities, but in a clearing in Central Africa. How could so many people be accommodated?

01:12:58.550 --> 01:13:14.550
To sleep 8,000 of the conventioneers, the brothers cut many thousands of poles, 30,000 bundles of grass, and built 17 of these sleeping shelters that radiated out from the seating area like great spokes of a wheel.

01:13:14.550 --> 01:13:34.180
Some of these were 700 feet in length. Put yourself in their place. Some of these people rode bicycles for two weeks, traveling more than 500 miles each way.

01:13:34.180 --> 01:13:43.180
Others walked four days through an area of wild beasts, then traveled two more by primitive bus to reach this assembly.

01:13:43.180 --> 01:13:56.310
All of Jehovah's Witnesses should have such a zeal for assemblies. Brother Nor spoke eloquently on, it is time to consider God's way.

01:13:56.310 --> 01:14:08.579
The brother on the right is translating the talk into Cebemba for the benefit of the assembled multitude.

01:14:08.579 --> 01:14:15.579
Another never to be forgotten part of this assembly was the singing of powerful hymns of praise to Jehovah.

01:14:15.579 --> 01:14:33.579
A choir of 1,010 led 18,000 voices. These hymns composed in the native languages by African brothers and sung with genuine zeal for Jehovah, left visitors with tingling spines and with tears of joy in their eyes.

01:14:33.579 --> 01:14:50.840
Lift up your eyes and view the fields, said Jesus, that they are white for harvesting. Today the harvest is great. The restoration of true worship expands to the ends of the earth.

01:14:50.840 --> 01:15:06.840
